# =============================================================================
# SiteFlow AI — Environment Template
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to `.env` for local use. `.env` is gitignored; this template
# (`.env.example`) is committed and must contain PLACEHOLDERS ONLY — never real
# values.
#
# IMPORTANT: The SiteFlow AI mobile app currently defines NO environment
# variables. The entries below are commented-out EXAMPLES that document the
# rules and naming pattern. Do not uncomment or invent variables the app does
# not actually use.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EXPO_PUBLIC_* variables are NOT secret.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Anything prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ is embedded into the app bundle at build
# time and is fully visible to every user. Use it ONLY for non-secret config
# such as public URLs or feature flags. Never put a key, token, or credential
# here.
#
# Example (illustrative only — not currently used by the app):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Private service keys belong to the FUTURE BACKEND — never the mobile app.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The mobile client must never hold any of the following. They live only in the
# backend's own server-side environment, which the app talks to over HTTPS:
#
#   - AI provider API keys (Anthropic, OpenAI, etc.)
#   - Database connection strings and credentials
#   - JWT signing secrets
#   - Any third-party private/secret key
#
# Do NOT add these to this mobile project's environment under any prefix.
# See `.claude/rules/security.md` for the full policy.
